1
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:02,439
Looking at the vibe of this city,

2
00:01:02,759 --> 00:01:03,679
this Prince of Chen

3
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:05,159
must be obsessed with Go.

4
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:08,439
It's rare to see you so clever today.

5
00:01:09,719 --> 00:01:11,959
I was just leaving you some room to shine.

6
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,560
I mean, you're a grown man.

7
00:01:13,599 --> 00:01:15,079
If you were worse than me at everything,

8
00:01:15,079 --> 00:01:16,359
wouldn't that be embarrassing?

9
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:18,079
Why not ride the wind, my lady,

10
00:01:18,319 --> 00:01:20,120
and soar ninety thousand miles high?

11
00:01:21,599 --> 00:01:22,359
Are you complimenting me?

12
00:01:22,359 --> 00:01:22,799
Yes, I am.

13
00:01:22,799 --> 00:01:23,920
Sincerely complimenting you.

14
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:27,560
I challenge you to a duel.

15
00:01:28,359 --> 00:01:28,920
If you lose,

16
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:30,840
hand over the late emperor's jade pendant.

17
00:01:31,799 --> 00:01:32,200
You...

18
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:33,439
A duel?

19
00:01:33,879 --> 00:01:34,359
What's the matter?

20
00:01:34,760 --> 00:01:35,959
And if you lose?

21
00:01:37,719 --> 00:01:38,280
If I lose,

22
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:39,200
I'll give you my life.

23
00:01:39,719 --> 00:01:40,359
Today,

24
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:42,480
I, Liu Heng, must fight you all

25
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:44,239
to the death.

26
00:01:44,239 --> 00:01:46,120
Hahahaha!

27
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:47,799
Playing Go?

28
00:01:48,519 --> 00:01:51,680
I've never been afraid of anyone.

29
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,079
You two play, then.

30
00:01:53,439 --> 00:01:54,359
I'll go take a stroll.

31
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:56,640
Ha!

32
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:58,840
Hey,

33
00:01:58,840 --> 00:01:59,560
all right, all right.

34
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:00,359
Come on.

35
00:02:00,879 --> 00:02:01,640
Today,

36
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,159
let's play Five-in-a-Row Go.

37
00:02:03,319 --> 00:02:03,840
How about it?

38
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:06,680
Five-in-a-Row Go

39
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,439
means whether horizontal or vertical,

40
00:02:08,639 --> 00:02:10,360
whoever lines up five pieces first...

41
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,039
Block!

42
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:21,960
Block

43
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:23,360
Diagonal

44
00:02:29,719 --> 00:02:29,919
Cut

45
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:33,120
Pincer

46
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:34,400
Tiger's Mouth

47
00:02:36,159 --> 00:02:36,400
Jump

48
00:02:39,439 --> 00:02:39,680
Knight's Move

49
00:02:40,639 --> 00:02:40,759
Crosscut

50
00:02:44,159 --> 00:02:44,479
Squeeze

51
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:45,400
Extension

52
00:02:47,759 --> 00:02:48,280
Jump

53
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:49,520
Knight's Move

54
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:51,560
Crosscut

55
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,400
Hand it over

56
00:02:58,479 --> 00:02:58,879
Ah

57
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:01,520
So Go here is this easy, huh?

58
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:02,919
I won ten games in a row.

59
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:04,159
Please call me

60
00:03:04,719 --> 00:03:06,199
Level 6 Go Master

61
00:03:07,639 --> 00:03:08,360
Did you win?

62
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,159
Uh

63
00:03:12,479 --> 00:03:13,280
I lost.

64
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:16,639
I don't know how to play Five-in-a-Row.

65
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:17,080
Oh dear

66
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:17,840
Forget it, forget it

67
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:18,520
It's fine

68
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:18,919
This round doesn't count

69
00:03:19,439 --> 00:03:19,719
Hey!

70
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,159
They're trying to back out!

71
00:03:21,319 --> 00:03:23,120
Anyone who loses Go in Chenwang City

72
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,479
is worse than a pig or a dog.

73
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:25,960
You all

74
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,879
must accept your loss like a true gambler,

75
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:28,680
and furthermore

76
00:03:28,919 --> 00:03:29,479
Ai-ya-ya

77
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:31,000
Hand over the jade pendant.

78
00:03:31,599 --> 00:03:32,520
The Prince of Chen arrives!

79
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:33,680
Ah

80
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:34,800
Hey

81
00:03:36,159 --> 00:03:36,439
The Prince of Chen

82
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:37,520
The Prince of Chen is here.

83
00:03:39,479 --> 00:03:40,039
Ah

84
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,639
Now we're saved.

85
00:03:42,199 --> 00:03:43,479
Someone will get us justice.

86
00:03:45,039 --> 00:03:46,400
Just who is it

87
00:03:46,719 --> 00:03:48,680
that dares act up in the Go house?

88
00:03:48,719 --> 00:03:48,919
Hey!

89
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:49,360
Hey, hey!

90
00:03:49,719 --> 00:03:50,800
Prince of Chen, Prince of Chen!

91
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,639
I'm Qi Zhi, the palace's special envoy!

92
00:03:53,039 --> 00:03:54,280
I came specifically to find you.

93
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:54,840
But

94
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,960
on the way I ran into

95
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,280
a crooked Go house

96
00:03:57,599 --> 00:03:58,439
and was forced to play.

97
00:03:58,439 --> 00:03:58,599
Hey!

98
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:00,280
You've got to get me justice!

99
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,000
I know.

100
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:03,520
Envoy Qi,

101
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:04,560
Your reputation precedes you.

102
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:04,879
Heh.

103
00:04:04,879 --> 00:04:05,960
Scared now, aren't you?

104
00:04:07,159 --> 00:04:09,319
But I'd like to ask you, Envoy Qi,

105
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,400
just now, did you win

106
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:12,400
or did you lose?

107
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,199
Oh, come on.

108
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,520
It's not a question of winning or losing.

109
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:17,199
They forced me to play.

110
00:04:17,199 --> 00:04:18,680
This clearly violates my... my... my...

111
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,079
basic rights as a citizen

112
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:21,199
of the Daliang Kingdom.

113
00:04:21,199 --> 00:04:22,399
You've got to get me justice here.

114
00:04:22,399 --> 00:04:24,120
I just want to ask,

115
00:04:24,959 --> 00:04:26,879
did you lose just now or not?

116
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:37,959
Yes.

117
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:43,199
What rights do losers have to speak of?

118
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:44,120
Guards!

119
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,199
Confiscate their belongings.

120
00:04:46,279 --> 00:04:46,959
Throw them in the dungeon.

121
00:04:46,959 --> 00:04:47,439
Hey!

122
00:04:47,439 --> 00:04:48,240
What?

123
00:04:48,399 --> 00:04:48,639
Hey!

124
00:04:49,319 --> 00:04:49,639
Hey!

125
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:51,079
Get in.

126
00:04:51,079 --> 00:04:51,759
Hey, hey, hey!

127
00:04:51,759 --> 00:04:52,360
Careful, careful, careful!

128
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,199
Thanks for your trouble.

129
00:04:53,199 --> 00:04:53,600
Thank you both for your hard work.

130
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,160
Thanks, much appreciated.

131
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:54,519
Thanks for your trouble.

132
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:55,920
This is all your fault.

133
00:04:56,319 --> 00:04:57,560
You drag me down every time.

134
00:04:58,079 --> 00:04:59,120
What do you know?

135
00:04:59,399 --> 00:04:59,879
This is called...

136
00:04:59,879 --> 00:05:01,000
luring the enemy in deep.

137
00:05:01,279 --> 00:05:02,199
Venturing into the tiger's den.

138
00:05:02,519 --> 00:05:04,000
After my on-site observation,

139
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:07,240
Chenwang City looks peaceful and thriving,

140
00:05:07,399 --> 00:05:08,839
but the Prince of Chen is actually

141
00:05:08,839 --> 00:05:10,279
twisted and cruel.

142
00:05:10,439 --> 00:05:11,000
Daliang

143
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,839
cannot fall into his hands.

144
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:16,000
The jade pendant is in his hands now.

145
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:17,199
Whether he's fit to be emperor

146
00:05:17,199 --> 00:05:19,120
isn't up to you anymore.

147
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:20,600
Chow time!

148
00:05:21,399 --> 00:05:22,360
Chow time, chow time!

149
00:05:25,279 --> 00:05:26,120
Hey, grab one for me.

150
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,360
Thanks.

151
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,120
Thanks.

152
00:05:32,199 --> 00:05:32,360
Hey!

153
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,160
Bro, bro, bro!

154
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:33,879
Why is it

155
00:05:33,879 --> 00:05:35,680
she gets three buns, and I just get one?

156
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,560
How can a hack match a Level 6 Go Master?

157
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,120
Is there no justice left?

158
00:05:40,839 --> 00:05:42,720
A plain bun is already a huge favor.

159
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:44,959
Let me out!

160
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,800
You want to get out?

161
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,839
You can leave anytime.

162
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:48,480
Really?

163
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:49,360
Just play Go,

164
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:50,759
defeat everyone in this prison,

165
00:05:50,959 --> 00:05:51,680
and we'll

166
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:52,920
carry you out on our shoulders.

167
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:53,600
What?

168
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,720
You wanna challenge us?

169
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,959
I'm a Level 6 Go Master, after all.

170
00:06:01,519 --> 00:06:02,279
Bring it on.

171
00:06:02,839 --> 00:06:04,279
Send out your strongest.

172
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,160
Strongest, huh?

173
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:08,120
If you wanna face our boss,

174
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:10,120
you've gotta get past us first.

175
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,720
That's right, that's right.

176
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,920
It's just Five-in-a-Row, right?

177
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:14,720
Bring it on!

178
00:06:15,279 --> 00:06:17,480
You dare embarrass yourself with that junk?

179
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,319
Here,

180
00:06:18,319 --> 00:06:20,120
we play real Go.

181
00:06:23,959 --> 00:06:24,480
What do we do?

182
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,519
I can't do this.

183
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:28,720
Aren't you decent at Go?

184
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,519
Five-in-a-Row, sure.

185
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:33,279
One more piece and I'm done for.

186
00:06:34,839 --> 00:06:35,639
Hmm.

187
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,800
Leave it to me.

188
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:39,439
Ha!

189
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:40,720
Ha!

190
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:41,680
Ha!

191
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:44,199
Let me see.

192
00:06:44,399 --> 00:06:46,639
Who do we have here?

193
00:06:47,279 --> 00:06:48,319
Professional rank-boosting.

194
00:06:48,519 --> 00:06:49,560
Level 6 guaranteed.

195
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,079
Hey, buddy.

196
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:12,720
Need a stand-in player?

197
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:13,560
Not playing.

198
00:07:14,199 --> 00:07:14,759
Come on, don't be like that.

199
00:07:15,399 --> 00:07:16,120
I'm a friend of Brother Niu.

200
00:07:16,759 --> 00:07:17,560
Cut me some slack.

201
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:18,160
Oho!

202
00:07:18,319 --> 00:07:19,079
Think you're a big shot, huh?

203
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:19,480
Come on, come on.

204
00:07:19,519 --> 00:07:20,319
Get out here, out here.

205
00:07:20,319 --> 00:07:20,600
Come on, come on.

206
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:21,759
Who were you talking about?

207
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:22,759
You, you, yes you.

208
00:07:22,759 --> 00:07:23,000
Don't be scared.

209
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:23,839
Come on, get out, out, out.

210
00:07:23,839 --> 00:07:24,800
Get out here.

211
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:27,240
I'm the West-City 9-Dan King.

212
00:07:27,319 --> 00:07:27,600
Please, have at me.

213
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:29,120
Please my foot.

214
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:29,800
Go back, go back, go back.

215
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:30,279
Showing off your height, huh?

216
00:07:30,279 --> 00:07:31,319
You think you're so tall.

217
00:07:31,319 --> 00:07:31,800
Did anyone call you? Did they?

218
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:32,360
You jump out the second you're called?

219
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:32,959
Come, come, come.

220
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:35,319
I was talking to you, ma'am.

221
00:07:35,319 --> 00:07:35,959
Come on, come on.

222
00:07:35,959 --> 00:07:36,720
Step out and let's spar.

223
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:37,000
Come on, come on.

224
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:37,959
Ma'am, ma'am, come on out.

225
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,279
Chenwang City Women's Champ here.

226
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,519
Please, enlighten me.

227
00:07:42,519 --> 00:07:43,000
Enlighten you?

228
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:43,639
My foot!

229
00:07:43,639 --> 00:07:44,720
Go back, go back, go back.

230
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,199
What time is it? Look at the time!

231
00:07:46,399 --> 00:07:47,120
Kids aren't home yet?

232
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:48,000
Are you taking care of them or not?

233
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:48,560
Are you making dinner or not?

234
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,040
The kids must be starving.

235
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:49,720
Hey, kid.

236
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,519
Huh?

237
00:07:54,839 --> 00:07:56,160
Little one, come over here.

238
00:07:56,279 --> 00:07:57,399
Come here a sec.

239
00:07:58,040 --> 00:07:59,240
Oh my.

240
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:01,079
So adorable!

241
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:03,120
I choose you!

242
00:08:06,439 --> 00:08:07,920
You're really Brother Niu's friend?

243
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,040
Of course.

244
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:10,639
Brother Niu told me

245
00:08:10,639 --> 00:08:11,839
if I want to test for Level 4 or 6,

246
00:08:11,839 --> 00:08:12,399
just come find you.

247
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:13,600
Can't go wrong.

248
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,319
Hehehe.

249
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,360
You know the rules, then?

250
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:17,560
Of course I do.

251
00:08:19,439 --> 00:08:20,639
For Level 4,

252
00:08:20,639 --> 00:08:21,560
it's 10,000 taels.

253
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,360
Level 6 is 20,000 taels.

254
00:08:23,639 --> 00:08:24,560
And Level 8?

255
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:25,560
That's 30,000 taels, of course.

256
00:08:26,279 --> 00:08:26,439
Here.

257
00:08:27,879 --> 00:08:28,600
I want Level 8.

258
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:32,600
What are you doing?

259
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:33,519
Don't do this!

260
00:08:33,519 --> 00:08:34,639
I'm Brother Niu's friend!

261
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,360
Go find your Brother Niu in prison.

262
00:08:36,759 --> 00:08:36,960
Huh?

263
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:37,559
This place

264
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:38,399
got shut down by the authorities

265
00:08:38,399 --> 00:08:39,840
a month ago.

266
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,039
The doors are open now

267
00:08:42,279 --> 00:08:44,080
just to catch stragglers like you.

268
00:08:44,639 --> 00:08:45,639
Cheating on certification exams.

269
00:08:45,639 --> 00:08:46,559
Three years in jail to start.

270
00:08:47,039 --> 00:08:47,279
Hmph.

271
00:08:48,399 --> 00:08:50,080
Look at you.

272
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:52,279
Couldn't even beat a kid.

273
00:08:52,879 --> 00:08:55,039
Got us both stuck suffering like this.

274
00:08:56,559 --> 00:08:57,960
What suffering did you go through?

275
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:58,960
I played Go all night.

276
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:00,679
I'm the one who did all the work, okay?

277
00:09:00,679 --> 00:09:01,039
Hey.

278
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:03,360
You think watching all night isn't tiring?

279
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:04,120
Get in.

280
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,600
I won't go in!

281
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,240
I...

282
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:10,799
Hey!

283
00:09:10,799 --> 00:09:11,919
Let me out, you!

284
00:09:12,679 --> 00:09:13,399
Liu Heng.

285
00:09:13,399 --> 00:09:13,919
Hey.

286
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:15,039
How did you end up in here?

287
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:17,679
Cheating trash like you

288
00:09:17,679 --> 00:09:18,720
should rot in jail forever.

289
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:19,440
Pah!

290
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,639
Cheating, huh?

291
00:09:21,639 --> 00:09:22,879
Hahahaha!

292
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:27,399
Isn't this Chenwang City?

293
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:29,320
How'd it end up like Jiwang City?

294
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:30,600
Hey!

295
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,559
Just let me out already.

296
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:34,039
I just hired a stand-in player, that's all.

297
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,240
A stand-in player?

298
00:09:36,519 --> 00:09:37,840
You actually hired a stand-in?

299
00:09:38,159 --> 00:09:39,480
Haha, how shameless!

300
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,759
A stand-in!

301
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,480
You hired a stand-in?

302
00:09:48,559 --> 00:09:49,360
Heh heh.

303
00:09:49,759 --> 00:09:50,919
What are you all laughing at?

304
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:53,039
Sigh.

305
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,120
Cost me 30,000 taels of silver.

306
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:57,519
Becoming emperor isn't easy, you know.

307
00:09:58,039 --> 00:09:58,840
30,000 taels?

308
00:09:58,919 --> 00:10:00,440
Hiring a stand-in costs that much?

309
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,559
I paid 30,000 for a Level 8 badge before,

310
00:10:05,919 --> 00:10:07,399
and ended up getting scammed.

311
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,080
Turned out to be a knockoff.

312
00:10:09,399 --> 00:10:09,879
Pah!

313
00:10:10,559 --> 00:10:11,720
It wasn't even a good knockoff.

314
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,320
Let me see.

315
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:16,519
Just one look.

316
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,799
Looks pretty realistic.

317
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:28,840
Realistic, my foot.

318
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,120
Have you ever seen a real one?

319
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:34,039
Good point.

320
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:36,080
Hey!

321
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,200
Give that back to me!

322
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:39,440
Hey.

323
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:40,399
My good sir.

324
00:10:42,039 --> 00:10:43,480
I'll give you this badge.

325
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,679
Just let us out, okay?

326
00:10:44,799 --> 00:10:45,159
How dare you!

327
00:10:45,639 --> 00:10:47,559
Forging a rank is punishable by death.

328
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,480
Keep your voice down.

329
00:10:49,639 --> 00:10:51,000
How is this forgery?

330
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,480
This is a gift.

331
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:53,639
Take a look.

332
00:10:53,639 --> 00:10:55,399
A Level 8 badge.

333
00:10:55,879 --> 00:10:57,399
With this badge,

334
00:10:57,759 --> 00:11:00,240
won't you rise through the ranks?

335
00:11:00,399 --> 00:11:01,919
Soaring straight to the top.

336
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,000
From now on,

337
00:11:03,039 --> 00:11:06,519
no more guard duty in this gloomy dungeon.

338
00:11:09,879 --> 00:11:11,080
Think about it again.

339
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,440
This matter,

340
00:11:12,639 --> 00:11:14,440
only you and I will ever know.

341
00:11:14,759 --> 00:11:16,480
I'm not even from Chenwang City.

342
00:11:16,639 --> 00:11:17,919
Once I'm out of here,

343
00:11:17,919 --> 00:11:19,600
I'll be long gone.

344
00:11:19,879 --> 00:11:21,120
What do you say?

345
00:11:21,360 --> 00:11:22,440
Hey, what are you doing with my stuff?

346
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,240
Keep it down.

347
00:11:34,039 --> 00:11:35,120
Everyone, hurry, go!

348
00:11:35,679 --> 00:11:36,759
If the boss doesn't go,

349
00:11:36,919 --> 00:11:37,879
neither do we.

350
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:41,240
Hey!

351
00:11:41,559 --> 00:11:42,440
Pretty clever, aren't you?

352
00:11:42,559 --> 00:11:43,360
Want it?

353
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:44,519
Want it?

354
00:11:44,759 --> 00:11:44,960
Give it to me.

355
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:45,559
Give it to me.

356
00:11:45,879 --> 00:11:46,120
Hey.

357
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:46,840
Stop teasing him.

358
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:47,399
Let's go.

359
00:11:47,399 --> 00:11:48,399
Hey, wait, wait, wait.

360
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,279
The Prince of Chen still has the pendant.

361
00:11:51,639 --> 00:11:53,200
We have to win that pendant back.

362
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,399
How can we win?

363
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:57,120
We can't even beat these prisoners.

364
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:58,320
Let alone the Prince of Chen.

365
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,440
Didn't they just say

366
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:01,639
they have some kind of boss?

367
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,200
If they're this good at Go,

368
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,519
their boss must be even better.

369
00:12:04,519 --> 00:12:05,480
Unbeatable in the world!

370
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:06,559
Let's break him out.

371
00:12:07,759 --> 00:12:08,600
Makes sense.

372
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:16,039
Are you here to rescue our boss?

373
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:18,480
How did you know?

374
00:12:19,279 --> 00:12:21,039
We admire the boss's Go skills.

375
00:12:22,799 --> 00:12:23,399
After you.

376
00:12:23,399 --> 00:12:24,200
After you.

377
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:25,080
Uh.

378
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,559
Thanks.

379
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,120
Thank you, sir.

380
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:42,879
Oh.

381
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:44,639
After you.

382
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:46,320
Thanks.

383
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:47,240
Ah!

384
00:12:47,639 --> 00:12:47,919
Retreat!

385
00:13:01,919 --> 00:13:03,559
So you're their leader.

386
00:13:12,279 --> 00:13:12,840
Who are you people?

387
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:14,320
Oh.

388
00:13:14,559 --> 00:13:15,200
Here's the thing.

389
00:13:16,159 --> 00:13:17,000
We heard that

390
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,840
you're the best Go player in this prison.

391
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:19,279
So,

392
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,039
we'd like to break you out.

393
00:13:20,919 --> 00:13:21,120
Come on.

394
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:21,879
Stick your foot out.

395
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:22,559
Come on.

396
00:13:22,879 --> 00:13:23,080
Come.

397
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:23,960
I'll do it myself.

398
00:13:29,639 --> 00:13:30,639
You know the Prince of Chen?

399
00:13:34,279 --> 00:13:35,480
I don't know him.

400
00:13:35,679 --> 00:13:36,519
Impossible.

401
00:13:37,679 --> 00:13:39,559
I saw it in your eyes.

402
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:41,519
Ouyang Yan.

403
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,120
Take his mask

404
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:43,919
off.

405
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:45,120
Oh.

406
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:47,399
Hey!

407
00:13:47,559 --> 00:13:48,919
I told you to take off his mask,

408
00:13:48,919 --> 00:13:50,039
not to hit him.

409
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:51,720
Didn't you tell me to hit him?

410
00:13:53,919 --> 00:13:54,720
Oh.

411
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,000
Oh my.

412
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:00,279
Hey, hey.

413
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:01,279
Whoa.

414
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,919
They're actually twins!

415
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:09,720
You mean to say

416
00:14:09,919 --> 00:14:11,840
you're the real Prince of Chen,

417
00:14:12,279 --> 00:14:14,000
Liu Xiaoyao?

418
00:14:17,759 --> 00:14:18,559
That's right.

419
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,080
I am Liu Xiaoyao.

420
00:14:20,879 --> 00:14:22,360
My younger brother is Liu Zizai.

421
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,120
My brother and I

422
00:14:25,559 --> 00:14:26,799
have loved playing Go since childhood.

423
00:14:28,559 --> 00:14:29,440
My brother worked extremely hard,

424
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,080
but unfortunately,

425
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,240
he lacked talent.

426
00:14:32,559 --> 00:14:33,919
He could never beat me.

427
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:37,720
But he was incredibly competitive,

428
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:39,759
constantly trying to outdo me.

429
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,039
In my eyes,

430
00:14:43,919 --> 00:14:45,840
Go is about cultivating one's character.

431
00:14:46,759 --> 00:14:48,080
But in his eyes,

432
00:14:48,639 --> 00:14:50,519
Go is only about winning and losing.

433
00:14:52,799 --> 00:14:53,600
Later,

434
00:14:54,799 --> 00:14:56,639
he forced me into a showdown.

435
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:00,879
Was it this game?

436
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,120
You lost.

437
00:15:10,919 --> 00:15:12,159
Well, we're done for.

438
00:15:12,879 --> 00:15:15,320
Even he can't beat the Prince of Chen now.

439
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,279
We should just leave.

440
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:18,120
Hey, wait.

441
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,559
At least let him finish.

442
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:27,039
At first, I thought I lacked Go skills,

443
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:28,440
which is why I lost to him.

444
00:15:29,399 --> 00:15:30,840
But then I realized

445
00:15:31,919 --> 00:15:32,360
he

446
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,639
seems to have cheated.

447
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:36,840
You mean

448
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,200
he only beat you by cheating,

449
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,559
and that's how he became Prince of Chen?

450
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:42,519
Exactly.

451
00:15:43,039 --> 00:15:43,759
No way!

452
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,799
He's that good and still cheats?

453
00:15:46,279 --> 00:15:47,360
Then what about

454
00:15:47,759 --> 00:15:49,360
those bizarre Go variants?

455
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:53,000
Those bizarre Go variants

456
00:15:53,639 --> 00:15:54,919
were also created by him.

457
00:15:55,879 --> 00:15:56,919
After he took power,

458
00:15:57,879 --> 00:16:00,000
he set up all sorts of game rules.

459
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:02,840
He ranked the players by levels,

460
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:04,360
where lower-ranked players

461
00:16:04,919 --> 00:16:06,559
are always weaker than higher ranks.

462
00:16:08,399 --> 00:16:09,159
And then,

463
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,240
step by step,

464
00:16:11,399 --> 00:16:12,840
he climbed to where he is now.

465
00:16:13,799 --> 00:16:14,600
So then,

466
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:16,519
come out with us,

467
00:16:16,879 --> 00:16:17,519
beat him,

468
00:16:18,039 --> 00:16:18,720
and reclaim the throne.

469
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:19,759
Then

470
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,639
you can return to the capital as emperor!

471
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:23,960
Are you stupid?

472
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:25,440
He's already a prince.

473
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,240
Why bother fighting?

474
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,600
We could just take him with us!

475
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:28,399
I'm not going.

476
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:30,279
Why not?

477
00:16:30,919 --> 00:16:31,360
Don't tell me

478
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:33,120
you want to rot in this prison forever?

479
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:35,240
Because

480
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,639
there's something I haven't finished.

481
00:16:39,799 --> 00:16:40,799
You want revenge?

482
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:44,879
I have to rescue them all.

483
00:16:46,039 --> 00:16:48,519
They were all imprisoned

484
00:16:48,639 --> 00:16:49,519
because they beat my younger brother.

485
00:16:50,919 --> 00:16:51,360
I can't

486
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,559
just abandon them.

487
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:53,639
Hmm.

488
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:55,559
So that's how it is.

489
00:16:58,120 --> 00:16:58,360
Then

490
00:16:58,879 --> 00:17:00,879
give me some time to think.

491
00:17:01,879 --> 00:17:02,200
How

492
00:17:02,559 --> 00:17:03,919
are we going to fight our way out?

493
00:17:03,919 --> 00:17:04,880
There are so many of them.

494
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:09,119
We're willing to lend you a hand.

495
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,400
Hey, what do you think you're doing?

496
00:17:15,119 --> 00:17:15,920
Hey!

497
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:16,720
Get down!

498
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:18,279
Hey!

499
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:22,359
You...

500
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:24,000
Just you wait!

501
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:25,319
I...

502
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:26,000
Phew.

503
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,279
We finally escaped without a scratch.

504
00:17:28,519 --> 00:17:29,559
Of course.

505
00:17:29,799 --> 00:17:31,799
Don't forget who this princess is.

506
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:32,960
Enough.

507
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:34,200
We barely escaped,

508
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,400
and we still have no plan.

509
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:36,759
Don't celebrate too soon.

510
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:40,400
I'll sneak into the Prince of Chen's home,

511
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,880
and break Liu Zizai's fingers,

512
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:44,880
then make him challenge you.

513
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:45,079
That way,

514
00:17:46,039 --> 00:17:47,000
you'd be guaranteed to win!

515
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:48,839
Are you stupid?

516
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,200
If your fingers

517
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:52,240
got broken,

518
00:17:52,519 --> 00:17:54,200
could you still accept a Go challenge?

519
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:56,039
Besides,

520
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:58,759
you'd become a city-wide

521
00:17:58,759 --> 00:18:00,359
wanted criminal.

522
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:02,200
You'd be in for it.

523
00:18:05,759 --> 00:18:07,039
My idea is

524
00:18:07,039 --> 00:18:08,200
you go to the Prince of Chen's manor

525
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:09,759
and beat Liu Zizai

526
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:11,160
into an idiot.

527
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:11,680
That way,

528
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:14,200
he'd forget how to play Go.

529
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,160
Oh.

530
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:15,359
But wouldn't I still become

531
00:18:15,359 --> 00:18:18,920
a city-wide wanted criminal too?

532
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:20,839
Do you think I'm stupid?

533
00:18:21,839 --> 00:18:24,079
The genius of my plan is this:

534
00:18:24,079 --> 00:18:25,720
once you beat someone into an idiot,

535
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:28,160
the idiot won't remember who did it.

536
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:30,319
So you won't be wanted.

537
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:31,359
But...

538
00:18:31,359 --> 00:18:34,000
Beating him senseless without killing him,

539
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,319
that's way too hard to control.

540
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:39,119
What if I accidentally beat him to death?

541
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:39,799
Then...

542
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:41,039
what do we do?

543
00:18:44,279 --> 00:18:45,720
Zizai is, after all, my own brother.

544
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:48,440
We shouldn't be so cruel.

545
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:52,920
What's wrong?

546
00:18:53,839 --> 00:18:55,480
Is the veil uncomfortable?

547
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:56,359
Hmm...

548
00:18:56,759 --> 00:18:57,519
No.

549
00:18:58,079 --> 00:18:58,759
It just feels

550
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:00,480
not very safe.

551
00:19:01,519 --> 00:19:02,359
No worries.

552
00:19:03,119 --> 00:19:04,920
Tonight I'll go to the blacksmith

553
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:06,200
and have a mask made for you.

554
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,759
Then I'll have to trouble the princess.

555
00:19:14,799 --> 00:19:15,440
Sit.

556
00:19:15,599 --> 00:19:16,400
Sit.

557
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:17,160
Everyone,

558
00:19:17,559 --> 00:19:18,480
sorry to interrupt.

559
00:19:18,799 --> 00:19:21,960
Today is a 7-dan and 8-dan Death Match.

560
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:22,920
Anyone

561
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,480
interested in placing a bet?

562
00:19:26,039 --> 00:19:26,400
Come on, come on.

563
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:27,759
I bet on Black.

564
00:19:28,079 --> 00:19:28,880
I bet on White.

565
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:32,920
What's going on here?

566
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:35,920
I have no idea.

567
00:19:37,279 --> 00:19:38,079
Waiter!

568
00:19:38,359 --> 00:19:38,680
Yes!

569
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:40,319
Hello, sir.

570
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:41,519
Next door,

571
00:19:41,519 --> 00:19:42,319
what's going on?

572
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:44,680
Oh,

573
00:19:44,839 --> 00:19:45,720
it's a Death Match.

574
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:48,799
Oh.

575
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:49,960
You're not from around here, are you?

576
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:50,440
Aiya,

577
00:19:50,519 --> 00:19:51,799
better not to ask.

578
00:19:52,079 --> 00:19:52,359
Wait!

579
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,200
Let me tell you something.

580
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,160
This thing

581
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,160
is called a Death Match.

582
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,519
Only when two people have a grudge

583
00:20:02,519 --> 00:20:04,000
can they initiate a Death Match.

584
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,759
And what if someone loses?

585
00:20:05,759 --> 00:20:08,200
Then they can never play Go again.

586
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,279
But by your logic,

587
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,160
wouldn't higher-ranked players

588
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:14,359
just bully the lower-ranked ones?

589
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:14,960
Oh, come on.

590
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:16,240
Of course not.

591
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:17,160
It absolutely

592
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,519
requires both parties' consent.

593
00:20:19,119 --> 00:20:19,839
Besides,

594
00:20:19,839 --> 00:20:21,559
who would, over some petty matter,

595
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:24,599
bet a lifetime of never playing Go again?

596
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:25,759
If you lost,

597
00:20:25,759 --> 00:20:26,759
it'd be worse than dying.

598
00:20:26,759 --> 00:20:27,440
Am I right?

599
00:20:28,039 --> 00:20:28,279
Hey.

600
00:20:28,279 --> 00:20:29,319
Everyone, look over there.

601
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:30,640
I heard

602
00:20:31,279 --> 00:20:32,240
that guy is an 8-dan,

603
00:20:33,319 --> 00:20:34,519
and he stole another man's wife,

604
00:20:34,759 --> 00:20:36,079
just relying on his high rank

605
00:20:36,079 --> 00:20:37,160
to bully others.

606
00:20:37,759 --> 00:20:38,240
Oh dear.

607
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:42,480
Uh...

608
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:43,279
Well...

609
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:45,039
You folks take your time chatting.

610
00:20:45,119 --> 00:20:46,799
Just holler if you need anything.

611
00:20:51,599 --> 00:20:52,680
You dare set me up?

612
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:53,680
I'll fight you to the death!

613
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,759
Go is meant to cultivate the mind.

614
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,720
How did it end up like this?

615
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:14,319
As the lord of a city,

616
00:21:14,759 --> 00:21:17,160
how can he tolerate such brutal matches?

617
00:21:18,519 --> 00:21:20,440
Aren't you always better than him?

618
00:21:20,519 --> 00:21:22,440
Beating him shouldn't be that hard.

619
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:25,519
But back then,

620
00:21:26,359 --> 00:21:27,599
I really did lose.

621
00:21:28,279 --> 00:21:29,200
Didn't you say

622
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:31,160
he only won because he cheated?

623
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:33,039
That's right.

624
00:21:33,599 --> 00:21:34,200
Back then,

625
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:36,279
the judge ruled I lost by five moves.

626
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,680
But based on our skill levels,

627
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:40,200
I couldn't have lost by that much.

628
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:42,480
But I couldn't find any proof.

629
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:44,759
So...

630
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:45,680
So what?

631
00:21:46,279 --> 00:21:48,039
So he'll lose again if he plays.

632
00:21:48,599 --> 00:21:49,400
Ugh!

633
00:21:49,799 --> 00:21:50,759
Knowing I can beat him

634
00:21:50,759 --> 00:21:53,400
but having no way to do it is unbearable.

635
00:21:54,319 --> 00:21:55,559
Even if

636
00:21:55,559 --> 00:21:56,839
we could beat him,

637
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:58,000
we can't make him agree

638
00:21:58,119 --> 00:21:59,200
to a Death Match with us.

639
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:02,519
He's so shameless,

640
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:04,039
he doesn't deserve to play Go with anyone.

641
00:22:05,279 --> 00:22:07,039
If no one plays Go with him,

642
00:22:07,599 --> 00:22:08,680
let's see how arrogant he can be.

643
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:15,480
Hey!

644
00:22:15,720 --> 00:22:16,920
I've got an idea!

645
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:19,039
Where's the

646
00:22:19,839 --> 00:22:20,039
Prince of Chen?

647
00:22:20,799 --> 00:22:21,680
Oh, he's inside.

648
00:22:21,799 --> 00:22:22,359
Oh.

649
00:22:23,559 --> 00:22:24,000
You're back.

650
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:24,359
Mm.

651
00:22:24,839 --> 00:22:25,680
A new mask.

652
00:22:25,680 --> 00:22:26,200
Try it on.

653
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:28,720
Alright.

654
00:22:33,759 --> 00:22:33,920
Mm.

655
00:22:34,759 --> 00:22:35,599
It fits perfectly.

656
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:38,880
Ah.

657
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:39,599
Thank you.

658
00:22:39,599 --> 00:22:40,359
I didn't think after all these years,

659
00:22:41,599 --> 00:22:43,119
I'd be so used to wearing a mask.

660
00:22:45,039 --> 00:22:45,759
Thank you,

661
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:46,519
Yan'er.

662
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:52,279
Yan'er?

663
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:55,240
We'll marry when we return to the capital.

664
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:57,200
Calling you that

665
00:22:57,759 --> 00:22:58,680
isn't strange, is it?

666
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:01,400
Uh...

667
00:23:02,519 --> 00:23:02,759
Um...

668
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,359
As long as you like it.

669
00:23:06,759 --> 00:23:08,119
If there's nothing else, I'll be going.

670
00:23:08,359 --> 00:23:09,160
Wait.

671
00:23:10,119 --> 00:23:10,559
My lord,

672
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:12,000
I'm tired too.

673
00:23:12,480 --> 00:23:13,359
Why don't we

674
00:23:13,519 --> 00:23:14,759
all turn in early tonight?

675
00:23:15,359 --> 00:23:16,160
Mm.

676
00:23:16,599 --> 00:23:17,240
Very well.

677
00:23:18,279 --> 00:23:19,519
Once we handle this matter,

678
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:21,240
I'll return to the capital with you.

679
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:23,440
Goodbye.

680
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:24,480
Mm.

681
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:35,880
I'll head off too.

682
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:37,400
This time,

683
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:39,519
you really care about the Prince of Chen.

684
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:41,440
Huh?

685
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:43,480
You're even

686
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:45,599
coming up with plans for him.

687
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:50,759
He's a good match.

688
00:24:03,759 --> 00:24:05,240
Come on!

689
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,759
Play a game of Go!

690
00:24:07,279 --> 00:24:08,680
We've got plenty

691
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,240
of time to spare!

692
00:24:10,839 --> 00:24:12,160
Come on!

693
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:13,680
Compete with us!

694
00:24:14,039 --> 00:24:15,240
We've got

695
00:24:15,519 --> 00:24:16,920
ten thousand taels of gold!

696
00:24:17,279 --> 00:24:18,759
Come on!

697
00:24:18,759 --> 00:24:20,279
Live it up!

698
00:24:20,799 --> 00:24:21,799
Men, women, young or old,

699
00:24:21,799 --> 00:24:23,279
all are welcome!

700
00:24:23,519 --> 00:24:24,519
Hehehe.

701
00:24:24,519 --> 00:24:25,920
This is so embarrassing.

702
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:27,240
Why do I have to hold the sign?

703
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:29,119
That's for not telling me your plan.

704
00:24:29,599 --> 00:24:31,160
It was clearly your idea, okay?

705
00:24:31,319 --> 00:24:31,960
Didn't you say

706
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:33,920
no one in Chenwang City can play Go,

707
00:24:33,920 --> 00:24:35,079
so the Prince of Chen would never agree?

708
00:24:35,279 --> 00:24:35,920
And once he disagrees,

709
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:36,920
he'll come out himself!

710
00:24:38,759 --> 00:24:40,160
But what if

711
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:41,000
this...

712
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:43,799
What if Liu Xiaoyao loses?

713
00:24:44,799 --> 00:24:46,240
Where would we get the money to pay?

714
00:24:46,599 --> 00:24:47,599
Are you stupid?

715
00:24:47,880 --> 00:24:49,160
If he can't beat Chenwang City's people,

716
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:50,480
how could he be the Left-Hand Go Sage?

717
00:24:51,519 --> 00:24:52,480
Well, who knows?

718
00:24:52,519 --> 00:24:53,200
Hold it up!

719
00:24:55,119 --> 00:24:55,599
Come on!

720
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:57,920
Come play Go!

721
00:24:58,160 --> 00:24:59,400
If no one comes...

722
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:00,839
So many people here,

723
00:25:01,279 --> 00:25:02,920
why won't anyone step up?

724
00:25:03,839 --> 00:25:04,799
Flying Dragon Go Hall.

725
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:06,599
Haha.

726
00:25:06,839 --> 00:25:08,519
We at Flying Dragon Go Hall want to see

727
00:25:08,519 --> 00:25:09,519
just who

728
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:10,920
is so arrogant.

729
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:11,680
Oh!

730
00:25:11,960 --> 00:25:13,079
Challenger number one!

731
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:13,920
May I ask,

732
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:15,720
how many of you will challenge us?

733
00:25:16,319 --> 00:25:16,599
Haha.

734
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:17,079
Master,

735
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:17,799
let me go.

736
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:19,200
Alright.

737
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:20,200
My name is Qing Yun.

738
00:25:20,519 --> 00:25:21,519
I alone will be enough.

739
00:25:22,319 --> 00:25:22,920
When you lose,

740
00:25:23,759 --> 00:25:24,480
don't try to weasel out!

741
00:25:25,119 --> 00:25:25,480
Please.

742
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:39,880
Alright.

743
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:41,480
Good.

744
00:26:02,839 --> 00:26:03,359
Impossible!

745
00:26:04,359 --> 00:26:05,359
My speed Go can't possibly lose!

746
00:26:05,599 --> 00:26:06,039
I...

747
00:26:06,119 --> 00:26:06,480
Alright.

748
00:26:06,519 --> 00:26:06,880
Wait a minute!

749
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:07,359
Wait!

750
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:08,279
Let me look again.

751
00:26:08,319 --> 00:26:09,119
Give me some time!

752
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:11,119
Come on,

753
00:26:11,599 --> 00:26:14,519
let's welcome the next challenger!

754
00:26:15,519 --> 00:26:16,359
Ah!

755
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:21,720
Master!

756
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:23,039
Master!

757
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:24,920
Don't call me Master anymore.

758
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:25,920
You can no longer play Go.

759
00:26:26,119 --> 00:26:26,519
Get lost!

760
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:27,920
Master...

761
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:28,680
Jing Bin,

762
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:29,519
you go up there.

763
00:26:30,759 --> 00:26:30,920
Me?

764
00:26:31,319 --> 00:26:31,920
Mm.

765
00:26:32,319 --> 00:26:32,920
What are you afraid of?

766
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:33,160
Get up there!

767
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:34,039
Go on!

768
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:35,599
Get going!

769
00:27:05,599 --> 00:27:06,359
Is there anyone else

770
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:07,720
who wants to challenge us?

771
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:09,079
I'm sorry, Master.

772
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:10,000
Anyone else?

773
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:10,920
Useless!

774
00:27:12,519 --> 00:27:13,720
I, your master, will go myself.

775
00:27:21,759 --> 00:27:24,359
Truly, I've met my match!
